  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"top ten\" PC games can be subjective, as it often depends on criteria like sales, critical acclaim, or cultural impact. However, here\u2019s a list that reflects a mix of popularity, influence, and critical recognition over the years:\n\n1. **Half-Life 2** (2004) - A landmark first-person shooter known for its storytelling, physics-based gameplay, and advanced AI.\n\n2. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt** (2015) - An open-world RPG praised for its deep narrative, expansive world, and complex characters.\n\n3. **Doom** (1993) - Often credited with popularizing the first-person shooter genre, it remains an iconic title in gaming history.\n\n4. **World of Warcraft** (2004) - A game that set the standard for MMORPGs, boasting a massive player base and rich lore.\n\n5. **Civilization V** (2010) - A turn-based strategy game that allows players to build and expand an empire, celebrated for its depth and replayability.\n\n6. **Counter-Strike: Global Offensive** (2012) - A competitive first-person shooter that has become a staple in esports, known for its tactical gameplay.\n\n7. **StarCraft II** (2010) - A hallmark of real-time strategy games, with a strong esports presence and extensive modding community.\n\n8. **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim** (2011) - An open-world RPG known for its vast world, modding community, and player freedom.\n\n9. **Minecraft** (2011) - A game that revolutionized the sandbox genre, allowing players to build and explore virtually limitless worlds.\n\n10. **Dark Souls** (2011) - Notable for its challenging gameplay and intricate world design, it has influenced many games with its mechanics and storytelling.\n\nThese titles represent a mixture of genres and have had significant impacts on gaming culture, gameplay design, or the industry as a whole. Keep in mind that personal preferences may vary, and different lists may highlight other titles based on various criteria.",
